      "action": "Initiate emergency acoustic pattern evolution at the Spire Resonance Vault: The Keepers' interpretive council, alarmed by the Families' demonstrated 60% decryption accuracy, orders a fundamental restructuring of the jamming array's harmonic rotation. The predictable synchronized pattern that the Families mapped is abandoned in favor of stochastic harmonic shifts generated by the Spire's internal mechanism vault — the triple-locked chamber whose keys only the Keepers possess. The cipher scripture interpreters develop a new \"scattering protocol\" that randomizes acoustic signatures across multiple frequency bands simultaneously, making pattern-mapping exponentially more difficult. The two shrine auditors stationed at the outer threshold are briefed on the new protocol and begin integrating the Council's liturgical cipher keys with the evolved acoustic framework for the consecration ceremony.",
      "outcome": "The acoustic pattern evolution is completed within four days of intensive work in the mechanism vault. The new scattering protocol introduces genuine randomness into the jamming arrays — the predictable harmonic rotation that the Families exploited is replaced by a stochastic system that changes every 7-13 minutes in unpredictable intervals. Perimeter sentinels test the new system by deliberately transmitting decoy signals; the Families' monitoring station on the canal approach captures only unintelligible noise fragments. The two cipher scripture interpreters who had privately doubted the Council's protection are reassured by the technical improvement and reaffirm their commitment to the alliance. The shrine auditors confirm the new protocol is compatible with the consecration ceremony's liturgical requirements. However, the Keepers note that the observation ceasefire with the Families technically prohibits \"new monitoring installations\" — the acoustic evolution is a modification of existing systems, not a new installation, but the Families may dispute this interpretation. The Keepers prepare a formal justification document should the Families protest.",
      "targetLocation": "Spire Resonance Vault",
      "tagChangeCount": 2,
      "chronicleEntryId": "90ec46e9-7dbf-46a8-b78a-95dc3eeb0fd2"
    }
